caption: Excellent.  Just like in Yangon.
Great outdoor dining situation. Excellent curated local beer selection. Heat lamps there on the colder days. Great addition to the neighborhood.
Great food and service! One of those places where you can order anything and love it
Wonderful drinks, delicious food, and lovely staff. Great outdoor seating!

Wow we had been wanting to try this place since they opened as we have loved and lost several Burmese places in the city over the years. Had held back as it's a bit pricey but boy was it ultimately worth it. Had the Smoked Tea Salad, Fish Curry, and chickpea gravy noodles and all were wonderful and unique, we are still reminiscing 24 hours later. I hope the latter will be added to the permanent menu. Ordered delivery and all food held up in the journey. Looking forward to sampling again, even in person one of these days (hoping outdoor seating is dog friendly!)
Great menu. The curries are exquisite and hearty. The drinks are pretty inventive but not nuts. I enjoyed it so much I've been back twice!

Outdoor and indoor seating had a nice ambience and their sake/wine cocktails were great. Loved all the food including braised pork and the noodle dish we had. Generous portions and have a yummy lunch to enjoy! This is an amazing, delicious new gluten free go to for me.
Excellent vegan options and comfy outdoor seating.

Flavor of food lacks depth.  Burmese flavors only hit initially but lacks true essence.  For a restaurant to name itself after Myanmar's capitol, I would expect more.  For a better representation of Burma's rich flavors, I suggest Asian Bowl on Queens Blvd in Forest Hills.  Ohn no khao swe here is authentic and only $6.99.

Drive for an hour but didn’t want to serve us because there was a miscommunication for reservation from the restaurants end.  Called to asked if they were open, said yes, asked that we are coming in an hour, the person on the phone said ok. Clearly miscommunication on reservation and you did offer us a table, wife was feeling cold so we said we will just take the food but a solid no, we didn’t pretend to make a reservation, why would we drive for an hour on that. Also the person on the phone said come by 9 because after we won’t take any more order.  Listen do whatever and say whatever to discredit my review but the fact was we wanted food because it’s home food that’s hard to find in nyc and you didn’t do anything for us just a solid no from the kitchen. So that’s how I feel.
Food is amazing!! Everything is fresh and the staff is extremely friendly. My family and friends adore coming here.
Great food.
Their menu is really amazing.
Cutest place, delicious food!! Highly recommended.

I live in the neighborhood and my girlfriend and I tried this restaurant on a whim several weeks ago.  We ate in the backyard based on the staff's suggestion. The ambiance was awesome, a total fantasy escape complete with ample heaters, mood lighting, and what I think was an intentionally worn wall mural of some kind of deity.  We ordered two noodle dishes and and a third course I unfortunately do not remember. The food was stellar, and the staff was friendly and accommodating throughout - some nice guys, just trying to run a quality Burmese restaurant off Classon Avenue...  I think this is a great spot.
Love the outdoor heated setup. Food especially the mohinga was great.

This place has a unique ambience and very friendly service. But the food is very pricey and you will have limited options in the menu. We ordered an appetizer 'Deep Fried Street Salad' which was priced $14 (not cheap at all) that had only romaine and a few onion-potato fritters. So I felt that paying $14 just for a plate of romaine is kind of too much. The main courses are also expensivethan they should be, but those are good quality food, so its still ok.
Expected more options in both the drink menu as well as in the food menu! The food tastes similar to bengali and bangladeshi food. Tastes good. The arrangement, cleanliness and presentation is great!
Food is delicious but their delivery situation is non existent.. they do pick up only (order ahead via doordash)

Our meal was exceptional as well as the wine our server recommended.  However,  he was a bit pretentious-- well, very pretentious.  It certainly offended my friend who I rarely see and was treating to a yummy meal.  In the end, we left with content, full bellies. Still, the mood of the evening shifted a bit after all was said and done. I have worked in fine dining for years and would NEVER compromise a guest's experience for my own personal enjoyment. Who does that? No one likes hearing "the industry" run down but just saying, folks. Once again, I'll wrap things up mentioning the food is ON POINT.
Excellent food
I have been going here for a long time and the service has always been amazing. I came in the other night and everyone there was extremely nice.

NYC needs more Burmese options but this is not really it. Food is quite bland and the price (example : $17 vegetarian garlic noodles) is not right given the lack of flavor.  They also routinely overbook reservations on busy nights.

Best Burmese food we’ve had in NY. We loved our deep fried street salad, but the garlic noodles were the real star of the meal. Super cute backyard seating and the staff was so lovely and accommodating. Looking forward to coming back.
As someone who has been to Burma more than a couple times, very impressed with the authenticity and diversity of menu!

Cool spot with impeccable service and a pop up style menu. Our server (gentleman with a Burton hoodie) was very knowledgeable, funny, friendly. There was another gentleman (maybe a bartender, with a beard) that was friendly and professional as well. Kudos to them for putting this experience over the top for my friends and i!  Food/Drinks: 8/10 The meatballs and salad with fried sweet potato were very tasty. I probably could have gone there and ordered a few rounds of the meatballs for just myself. I ordered the fish curry and it had a great flavor, but it was nothing extraordinary or over the top memorable for me. The drinks however were excellent and very unique!  Value: 3/5 Unfortunatley this place carries the pop up vibe. Limited menu, smaller portions, higher prices. 2 appetizers split between three people with an entree, and splitting a dessert three ways was just enough to keep me satisfied for the night. One drink a piece and our totals came out to about $60 per person before tip. The portion sizes are fair but for $20-27 entree range, in my perfect world, i was hoping for a little more. Even the rice bowls were fairly skimpy. For the quality of the food, service, and location, i think overall the value of this establishment is fair.  Service: 5/5 No real comments other than exceptional service from the two gentleman listed above. They had knowledge of the gluten free items and different ways to prepare them. They were funny, friendly, and everything else was perfect!  Experience: 4/5 I am unaware of what outdoor seating may exist outdoors in the back, but we were say in the front under a newly built cove of some sorts. It was finished just before we arrived! It had space heaters and a roof. Beautiful flower decore.  If you’re in the area, definitely a place to check out. For me, the prospect and crown heights areas have a lot more to offer that I have been excited about
Attention Carnivores: the Pork is one of the best things you can do for yourself in 2020. And vote!

Extremely kind and friendly staff. I loved the garlic noodles with shrimp and onion fritter starter. I also recommend the coconut chicken soup. I live in the neighborhood and it's constantly busy here, and for good reason!

Price: $$  Accessibility: the location has outdoor dining and the bathroom was wheelchair accessible.  Food: was great we got the noodles with shrimp and the fish curry! You have to mix the noodles to fully experience it with the spicy side.  Staff: amazing! Mason was awesome and upbeat and Daniel gave me a cozy space blanket when I got cold when he really didn’t have too!  Parking: there’s a paid parking around the area

Flavors of every dish  I had are above and beyond. Didn't have high hopes for the pumpkin stew expecting it to taste bland. Man, I was wrong!  Pumpkin pieces are melting with every bite releasing complex flavors. It's great! Tea leaves salad is another recommendation. So simple, cabbage based, but so flavorful. Topped everything with yuzu sour ale, first one of that kind I had this summer of 2020.

Update: here is the reservation you’re claiming I didn’t have Daniel. We came to ask if we could be seated in the back and potentially put our names down  You have a very wonderful and polite staff. Be more life them✌🏾  We had a very strange interaction with the  owner/manager Daniel. Not going to a place where I do not feel welcomed. Disappointing because I was excited to try the food

Ok, first of, I had a reservation.  We came over to ask if we could be seated in the garden as we had been told previously that that was ok.  It was strange that you saw us standing right in front of the restaurant when one of your staff came to ask you if you could accommodate our request but you chose not to speak to us directly and let us know if it was possible or not. I think that was very rude of you.  Josey  11 hours ago We had a very strange interaction with the  owner/manager Daniel. Not going to a place where I do not feel welcomed. Disappointing because I was excited to try the food Like  Share Response from the owner 5 hours ago Sorry you feel that way. Anymore details about the interaction? Was it about me not taking your name down for a waitlist because we were already overbooked? As you can see in so many other reviews we pride ourselves on the friendliness of our service and our welcoming attitude. But like all other social interaction, these things go both ways. There is a single other negative review (on Yelp) about the service and it was precisely about issues with being on a waitlist versus having a reservation. Our reservations have priority and when we do a waitlist it's when we think there is a chance to accommodate people without a reservation. Since that review, I have been very careful about putting people on a waitlist as it seems to sometimes create confusion and people get mad when a reservation gets seated in front of them after they have been put on a waitlist. I always try to say yes, but it has sometimes backfired and I'm starting to no. So far the only issues we've had about our service in general as been related to the waitlist and people feeling entitled to it or from it. We try to do the right thing by everyone but sometimes it's just not possible. I wish it didn't have to be this way and that you can forgive me for making you feel unwelcomed. If you change your mind, try to make a reservation and hopefully everything will be much smoother. -Daniel
Food was amazing. There’s outdoor seating in the front and back. Staff were super nice and attentive. Would recommend if you’re in the area and looking to try out Burmese food!

Amazing food and extremely friendly staff! I've had Burmese food in Yangon and this was the best I've had in the US. The onion fritters!! and mohinga are a must. As well the tea leaf salad. Don't forget the wine cocktails. Their beer selection is great also! It's a special place and I'm happy to see rare Burmese cuisine addition to the usual NYC dining options.
Super meh. The food was pretty pricey and hit or miss on flavor. Tea leaf salad was great but most other things were less so. Actually was quite disappointed.
It was very yummy!  We got take out
Great service and owner was very kind.
Food is delicious!! Great catering service!!!

NYC needs a good Burmese restaurant. This is a Burmese-style restaurant and as such it's ok. The green tea salad is a good *approximation* but it lacks the punch that comes with roasted chilli flakes in the more authentic places. Alas, NYC doesn't have what Boston area Yoma offers, or Toronto, or the West coast. This restaurant is a nice hip Burmese-style spot. But I will keep looking.
So so delicious. Highly recommend! Tea leaf salad and chicken curry were amazing. Great service and owner was very kind. I’ll definitely be back.
Order the tea leaf salad!
Ordered the braised pork for takeout, it was really great!

The best food I have had in months! The tea leaf salad was bursting with flavor, and the tomatoes and chickpeas were perfect accents. The prawn curry was uncomplicated and full of flavor but not overwhelmingly spicy. Shrimp were soft and perfectly cooked. The real show-stopper was the lemongrass fish soup, with its oozy boiled eggs and crunchy sweet fried onion fritter. The dried shrimp relish with slices of cucumbers was great on its own drizzled with lime, but also a nice fishy salty accent to the curry and soup. Even the plain white rice was cooked to perfection. Will absolutely be ordering from here again and telling my friends.
Delicious tea leaf salad and tamarind limeade!

Authentic, delicious Burmese food. We have only gotten take out so far (coz COVID-19), and all the stew dishes (the pork and the chicken curry)  have been amazing. We also love the mango pawn salad, which is very refreshing and perfect for the summer!
Delicious!
Just yum. I can't get enough of this place, their teas, tea leaf salad and mango chicken are 100%.
Amazing food!  Can't wait until we can sit and eat here.

The Lemongrass chicken curry has a nice cinamon flavor. It's delicious. The Shan gabanzo tofu is delicate and the accompanying tamarind dipping sauce has a addicting floral scent. Restaurant is tastefully decorated, lovely staff. This place is a gem!
Awesome food and owners. Can't wait until they get some Burmese beer as well
Delicious food, excellent service. The sauce on the potato appetizer is out of this world. I could drink it by the liter
The food was very disappointing.Fitters were soggy and noodles were over cooked.
Great food, great service - we enjoyed our dinner here ! It felt authentic - the couple next to us was from Myanmar and said it was legit. Would def go back !
Amazing food and everyone is so nice! Still hasn’t fully opened but I can’t wait to come back to the full drink and food menu!

Cute spot. Still in pre-opening as of this review. The chef has creative takes on familiar dishes and adds a unique flavor to the noodles and curries. The wait staff are amazing as well. Can't wait to come back when it's fully open.
Great food!
